The study population comprised of smallholder farmers actively engaged in soybean production within selected districts of Eastern Province which will be Sinda, Katete, Kasenengwa, Chadiza, Chipata, Petauke, and Chipangali. Given the diverse nature of smallholder farming and the specific focus on soybeans, efforts were made to include farmers from various agro ecological zones mentioned above, with different levels of experience in soybean cultivation, and varying degrees of engagement with formal insurance companies such as professional insurance, Madison General, Zisc, Nico, which are based throughout the eastern province.
