3.3. Sampling Procedures
A mixed-methods sampling approach was utilized, combining probability (Stratified random) sampling for quantitative data with purposive (non-probability) sampling for qualitative data. Stratified random sampling was used to select a few districts within Eastern Province which were Sinda, Katete, Kasenengwa, Chadiza, Chipata, Petauke, and Chipangali. Farmers were stratified by their level of soybean production (2 acres-16 hectares) to ensure each group is proportionally represented that are representative of smallholder soybean farming communities and have experienced climate related agricultural challenges.
