A minimum of 200 smallholder farmer respondents were targeted for the quantitative survey, which is considered sufficient for statistical analysis and achieving reasonable accuracy according to (Morgan & Cohen, 2008), (Manion, & Morrison, 2018).
For the qualitative component, approximately 15 key informants were selected to ensure data saturation across all supply-side perspectives. To ensure the supply-side perspective was captured with clinical precision, the researcher conducted 15 stakeholder interviews with key informants from four market leaders. Professional Insurance, Madison General, ZISC, and Nico Insurance. In contrast to quantitative surveys that rely on margin of error formulas, this qualitative approach utilized the principle of Data Saturation.
