2. Key informant interviews- see (Appendix 2 on page 31): Conducted with relevant stakeholder’s farmers and insurance companies using a semi- structured interview guide. These interviews will gather qualitative data on the supply-side challenges in developing and delivering appropriate crop insurance products for smallholder soybean farmers. They will also provide insights into policy and regulatory frameworks affecting agricultural insurance.
3.6 . Data Analysis
Qualitative Data Analysis: Qualitative data from key informant interviews and open- ended questions in farmer surveys were transcribed and analyzed using thematic analysis. This rigorous process involved familiarization with the data, initial coding, searching for themes, reviewing themes, defining and naming themes, and producing the report. Thematic analysis helped in understanding the underlying reasons for low uptake, the specific challenges faced by both farmers (demand-side) and insurance providers (supply-side) in the soybean insurance market, and potential strategies for enhanced financial inclusion. Quantitative Data was analyzed using descriptive statistics.
