1. Inaccurate Pricing: Risk of overpricing (making it unaffordable) or under-pricing (threatening company solvency).
2. Wrongly Set Triggers: In Area Yield Index Insurance (AYII), if the "normal" average yield is incorrectly calculated, a payout might not be triggered even when farmers suffer loss.
